---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PersonalBaseLayout from '../layouts/PersonalBaseLayout.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const pageTitle = "Now";
---

<PersonalBaseLayout title={pageTitle}>
	<h1>Personal</h1>
	<p>
		I've had a lot happening lately. I'm giving my first talk on Saturday so that's taken 
		up a lot of time but it's almost here! I've been job hunting which has been kinda 
		dispiriting honestly. But I'm keeping my head up and doing my best still. I've been 
		trying to play more games recently and just do more leisure activities to break my
		habit of all work and no play.
	</p>
	<div class="divider" style="padding-left:4em"></div>
	<h1>Projects and Things I'm Playing With</h1>
	<p>
		Otome Jam Project - I'm the programmer for a team doing an Otome Jam project about a 
		demon coming into your room and cheering you up. I'm really excited to be working with 
		a team again!
	</p>
	<p>
		.Nani Converter - I making a little program to take my weird format of script writing,
		which is an unholy combo of screenplay format and game script syntax, and have it 
		convert that text into properly formatted naniscript. I might make it work for LightVN
		format too but I'm not sure honestly. 
	</p>
	<p>
		Scope Testing Project - I'm working on a small project/experiment. In this case the goal 
		isn't really to finish the full game as concepted in my brain but rather a kinda learning 
		in public type thing. I plan on using it to not only test how small I can make an MVP, but
		also my ability to iterate and keep scope small. Not sure how it'll go honestly.
	</p>
	<div class="divider" style="padding-left:4em"></div>
	<h1>Media</h1>
	<dl>
		<dt><h2>Games</h2></dt>
		<dd>Tomodachi Life</dd>
		<dd>Gnosia</dd>
		<dd>Heart of the Woods</dd>
		<dt><h2>Most Recent Movie</h2></dt>
		<dd>Puss in Boots: The Last Wish</dd>
		<dt><h2>Books</h2></dt>
		<dd>A Complete Guide to Character Rigging for Games</dd>	
	</dl>

		<script>
			import '../scripts/menu.js'
		  </script>
</PersonalBaseLayout>

<style>
	main {
		margin: auto;
		padding: 1rem;
		width: 800px;
		max-width: calc(100% - 2rem);
		font-size: 20px;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}
	img {
    float:left;
	padding: 2%;
	}
	.astro-a {
		position: absolute;
		top: -32px;
		left: 50%;
		transform: translatex(-50%);
		width: 220px;
		height: auto;
		z-index: -1;
	}
	h1 {
		font-size: 4rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1;
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 0em;
	}
	.link-card-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(24ch, 1fr));
		gap: 2rem;
		padding: 0;
	}

</style>
